<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-760] Generated client code does not set or check the sequence ID in messages</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-760</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The sequence ID is never set in the generated client code. It is also never checked. This means that if you continue to use a connection after a socket timeout the returned results can arrive out of sequence. When this happens an exception should be thrown so that incorrect results are never returned.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12462260">THRIFT-760</key>
            <summary>Generated client code does not set or check the sequence ID in messages</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
